																		2014 Guide Overhaul
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/aelanna" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(334454); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=334454&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610224094" alt="Aelanna" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=334454)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/aelanna" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(334454); return false;" >Aelanna</a></span> <span class="odate time_1398273703 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">23 Apr 2014 17:21</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2018052">
									

<p>This guide has been rewritten as part of the 2014 background guide overhaul. The original version of this page can be found in archive form <a href="/scp-object-classes-arc">here</a>.</p>
<h1><span>Changes From Original Version</span></h1>
<ul>
<li>The primary definitions of <em>Safe</em>, <em>Euclid</em>, and <em>Keter</em> have been reoriented primarily around difficulty of containment, as is colloquially used on the site.</li>
<li>The list modules have been removed to make room and cut down on the number of tabs.</li>
<li>The common rule of thumb that states that sapient entities should be <em>Euclid</em> by default has been codified.</li>
<li>Primary and Secondary classifications have been separated for clarity.</li>
<li><em>Thaumiel</em> as an object class has been codified.</li>
<li><em>Decommissioned</em> has been removed from the in-universe guide and moved to the Writing Guide.</li>
</ul>
<h1><span>Credits</span></h1>
<p>This guide was written with the help and input of all senior staff members.</p>

