			<div class="content" id="post-content-2839292">
									

<p>Heimal isn't an official class. It technically falls into the narrative object class category, along with Maksur, Apollyon, and most other SCPs that use one off classes. That means that it's there to give a hint to what's going to happen in the article and set the initial tone.]</p>
<p>In regards to definition, the best one I've heard is that Heimal is the Foundation containing something that was already containing or counteracting another anomaly. While this could technically fall into the SEKT spectrum, I do like seeing more narratively driven classes.</p>

