														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4471112">
									

<p>This guide is meant to be reflective of how object classes are understood on the site. If you have a way of doing things you think is better than the current system, then use that system in an article and see if it catches on.</p>
<p>However, given that ACS (which was also a massively-successful optional renovation of the Object Class system) shows no signs of being added to this page (and staff are pretty hesitant to switch up the SEKTEN system for obvious technical reasons), your system would have to be near-totally accepted to be listed in this guide.</p>
<p>It seems like something that would be more appropriate in the <a href="/esoteric-classes-complete-list">Esoteric Classes Guide</a>, under Subclasses, when a successful mainsite article uses it.</p>

