<p>It only becomes an official class if enough people use it. Since there is only one article with the <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">Apollodorus</span> Appolyon<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-56467-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-56467-1')">1</a></sup> class, it isn't canon enough to be in this guide or have an official definition beyond what's hinted at in the article.</p>
<p>You'll notice that there are a couple other unofficial object classes on the site that don't have specific definitions (like Enochian or Embla).</p>
