			<div class="content" id="post-content-3886007">
									

<blockquote>
<p>How many main series apollyons do there have to be before it becomes an official object class</p>
</blockquote>
<p>More than what we have (which is what? 2?). Beyond that, couldn't say.</p>
<p>Establishing a new Object Class is not like making, say, a new canon or GoI. There's no official number of articles where an object class suddenly becomes official. Rather, it's the result of site culture pushing towards it. And this process shouldn't change, IMO, as altering or adding new Object Classes kinda goes against the at-a-glance function they serve. Make too many of them, make the process too easy, and the system collapses.</p>

							</div>

								
